cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.CV, cs.DS

The paper proposes a novel type of model that combines interpretable and black-box models for classification. This falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the need for model interpretability, which is a topic in computer security (cs.CR). The proposed model involves capturing subspaces, which is a technique commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the optimization problem is solved using the accelerated proximal gradient method, which is a technique in optimization and data science (cs.DS).
